  </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Was I wrong, looking for some perspective...</span><hr size=1> Well, died again today, no big deal...I do that alot, but the circumstances around it are what got my ass in knots.  <br>
<br>
Here goes:  I was in Warsilk's Woods, kicking around the Brutes and had just gotten the intact choppers of a Pygmy(for my next shackle quest), when I hear someone hollering for more folks at the Giant Fortress.  I had been LFG for about an hour or so, as soloing can get a bit boring and inquired, I was accepted...C'mon down!  <br>
<br>
Woot omw, well I get there and it is a troll shammy named Littelsarge from Dark Reign(I think) and a Necro plus another caster.  Well, as I'm invited in, the shammy pulls an Evergreen(yellow to me, no problem).  During the course of the battle, I seem to be the only one hitting it with anything...kept announcing MENDING when I was down a bit, but the shammy kept burnin' mana on heals(which is fine) till he was oom.  That was not a problem, he jumped up and started poking it with his spear, by then I'm down to 2 bubs of health and no mend...don't see the Necro's pet anywhere anymore, and I'm honestly not sure if it died or he called it off.  With a couple of smacks, I'm down to one bub and I back off and start FDing...shammy hollers &quot;Everyone melee!!&quot;.  Kickass I think, its down to less than a bub of health and they can take him if my FD ever works.  Then what really lit my fire happened, one caster says oom(duh) and the other says, &quot;No I cannot melee.&quot;  Well, I died and lost the exp I had acquired thru the evening, very annoying for someone as casual a player as myself.  That would have been np except for the, &quot;I can't melee&quot; thing.  With the beastie down that low, it wouldn't have been a big deal to stand up and poke it a bit(they all 3 were at full health, none gone whatsoever).<br>
<br>
To his credit, Littelsarge keeps saying sorry it happened.  I said it wouldn't be a problem, if the others hadn't point blank refused to help, so I literally said thanks alot for that(inflamatory, I know).  One of them then makes a smartass remark that sent me over the edge, so I tell them buh bye and disband.  The shammy then starts giving me tells saying how &quot;gay&quot; I am, and neither myself or anyone from the Sentinent will be welcome in his guilds groups, etc.  I asked him how he can be pissed at me when I died, no one else did...so obviously the could have handled taking the offense on the giant?  So to that he just tells me I'm f%&amp;*ing lame and stop talking to him.<br>
<br>
Well, I went back and got my stuff and moved on, thinking back on it, maybe I did get too mad...and more importantly, I'm worried my actions reflected poorly on the Guild as a whole.  Whaddaya think?<br>
<br>
Thanks <p><a href="http://jofus73.homestead.com/files/sakki.jpg
"target="web"><img src="http://jofus73.homestead.com/files/sakki.jpg
" border="0"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ushoumai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shoumai</A> at: 3/7/01 1:58:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/bthesentinent.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ilrissa>Ilrissa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Officer</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#333333>(3/7/01 9:12:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Lazy or chicken?</span><hr size=1> The other afternoon I was in a group at the KFC stand at SK. The group wants to keep pulling Avocets. These are all conning red to Elmarra. I keep saying they are going to resist. But they pull anyway. Guess what they resisted everything in my bag of tricks. I have been resisted before so this is nothing new but the group is caster heavy and I am the highest one.<br>
<br>
We have a Ogre warrior a DE thief, Cleric, Enchanter, Mage, and a Wizard. The ogre is the lowest. The ogre is bashing away and the Thief is back stabbing. The cleric is casting one heal after another. The mages air pet is in there but doesnt look like it is doing alot of damage. Me I am casting my fingers off resist resist resist. The ogre goes down and everyone is taking a beating. I am oom so into the fray I go. We won just barely.<br>
<br>
A little while later they pull another one. I tell the group casters that if it resists to melee right away. This time it goes alot better. The ogre is only down 2 bubs and the thief one. All I did was apply a little common sense.  IF YOU ARE GOING TO BE RESISTED, HIT IT! Dont wait for the Tanks to die and then have to melee it by yourself. I dont know about my counterparts but I am dishing out 18 points of damage when I do hit. I am quite sure if someone takes a hundred points off A MOB the melee guys arent going to complain to much.<br>
<br>
The wizards guide says to try and do without a weapon after lvl 20. Well I am 24 now and you can have my staff when you pry it from my cold dead fingers. Ive taken my share of beatings at the hands of angry MOBs but I stand my ground melee. If I have mana I try to root. and when all else fails I press my hot key for /loc. and go down swinging.<br>
<br>
Have your casters melee if they are resisted it takes less mana for your healer to heal a caster than it does a tank. Plus if their spells arent doing anything they arent doing anything, and dont deserve the xp or the loot.   <br>
<br>
Feel free to NUKE my post. Just be careful it might be resisted, and I still know how to melee. Do you?<br>
<br>
Elmarra Silverhand<br>
Wizard of the 24 Circle <br>
