But when I wasnt dual weilding steins, you better believe I was stabbing away with my sacraficial dagger or dragoon dirk every chance I got.  I tried to keep my melee skill up as high as I could.<br>
<br>
And as far as not being invited into a group by anyone in his guild or him,.........so.  I could care less if that was the route him or they wanted to go (not saying that's how it is, but if it were so).   With some of the stuff he said Id look at it as one less idiot I would have to worry about accidentally grouping with, and being sorry I did afterwards.  Heck at least you told them you were leaving before you disbanded, which is a good thing to practice.  <br>
<br>
So all in all, I dont think you were wrong.  Ive been in your shoes to where all my nights work had basically been thrown away in a matter of minutes because of something someone in my group could have prevented.  And if things aren't going well in your group, why not let them know how you feel and disband? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/utaladan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taladan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Member</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#333333>(3/7/01 2:43:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Wrong?  You?  Bah!</span><hr size=1> Along Bramblers lines it is funny that a group in their mid 20's could be full of what appears to be several that really have not idea how to do thier part well.<br>
<br>
A Shaman OOM?  Caster even?  And a pet that's in a coma?<br>
<br>
Yep definetly a bad group from what you say.  But to top it off the &quot;personal&quot; conflict between you and the Shaman just bites.  I have seen, well heard, much of this &quot;My Guild wont this and wont that&quot; lately and it's getting a bit old. Idle threats is all .. they simply are trying to inflict pain by doing so. <br>
<br>
I personally would not take the words of any one member of a guild, especially a loose cannon like this one seems to be, as  any indication of anything more than a waste of my time reading it. They no more represent thier Guilds veiw than a tree stump would.  Which in a way is good .. cause if they did .. would be a bad reflection upon them and I would consider it no loss on my part .. and much on theirs.<br>
<br>
Just play your game Bro, you do it well, and take these events in stride. They can ruin a night or two even .. but don't let them stick to you.  Have fun .. rule number one.<br>
