 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/uaonedil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aonedil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Officer</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#333333>(3/7/01 6:01:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Was I wrong, looking for some perspective...</span><hr size=1>   Ok, let me give you 2 situations here that I was involved in. 1st I&lt;Aon, and group was all 37-41ish&gt; was with some guildies in Lguk, &lt;Mord, Tey, Taan&gt; and when the Mob decided to start running away, just for fun, I stopped attacking it and told them to melee it to death. Now granted, it was a blast, but it took about 3 min to kill the thing, and it had a sliver of life. So instead of dishing out 40 points of damage in 3 min, they could have meded up and nuked for 400, in half the time.<br>
<br>
  Situation 2. I &lt;Meudir, we were lvl 15&gt; was in Tim Deep with Crimsyn hunting skellies, and it went bad. I was oom, Crim was running around kiting the skellie, while I was medding. Now if I stepped in there and tried to melee it, I would have died. No question. So I medded while Crim kited and finally got the kill shot on it.<br>
<br>
  That's just my 2cp on the whole caster meleeing deal, but like Sent said, it just sounds like on of those Moron groups. Lord knows we've all had them. Just make sure to put them on the DUMBASS list and never group with them again.<br>
<br>
Aonedil/Meudir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/uahazimandius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ahazimandius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(3/7/01 9:38:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Was I wrong, looking for some perspective...</span><hr size=1> Hmmm. I notice some parallels here with my post on the monk named Feriss. If you haven't read it check it out. What I did was a /w all &quot;guild in question&quot; and contacted someone to get an officer and told them of the threat that had been made. As in your case the guild had no idea of the propositioned threat and didn't support it. I imagine the guild in question had some choice words for their guildie for overstepping his authority and making their guild look bad. <br>
<br>
That might be worth noting as what I feel is the most effective response to date. I know of another situation involving the Sentinent once where I turned the problem over to the guild and justice was served. Seems to be the most level headed approach although if you get better ideas lemme know them :-). <br>
<br>
